{
  "name": "VLA Policy Runner (LIBERO)",
  "description": "Run any vendored VLA policy (Pi0 / SmolVLA / DiffusionPolicy / DROID-DP) on LIBERO via the 5-node General Policy Adapter pipeline (env_adapter stages 1/5 + policy_adapter_vla stages 2/3/4, 1:1 with vlaworkspace's RobotAdaptor + ModelAdaptor methods). Each config-owning node has a single `select` dropdown whose options come from filesystem discovery: **adapt_env_to_canonical** lists `adapters/robots/*.py` (`robot`); **adapt_canonical_to_model** lists `adapters/models/*.py` (`model`); **predict** lists `policies/*.py` (`policy`) plus a `checkpoint_path` (per-experiment). Each adapter / policy file owns its own `DEFAULT_KWARGS` transcribed from upstream Hydra YAMLs — drop a new .py in the folder = new dropdown entry; delete a file = option vanishes. Switch model = change two dropdowns (model + policy) and the checkpoint_path. The action-side nodes (**adapt_model_to_canonical** and **adapt_canonical_to_env**) carry no config. Topology (gym-like, 2026-06-10): env_libero__reset emits metadata only; seed_obs (env_libero__observe_egocentric) pulls the first-iter loop carry (agentview/wrist/state); inside the loop, iterIn fans out to adapt_env_to_canonical → adapt_canonical_to_model → predict → adapt_model_to_canonical → adapt_canonical_to_env, whose JSON action chunk feeds env_libero__step_continuous (control signals only); loop_obs re-observes per iter; evaluate (trigger ← step.info) harvests metrics.",
